==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Benumb
<hw>Be*numb"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Benumbed</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Benumbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>binomen</ets>, p. p. of <ets>binimen</ets> to take away, AS.
<ets>beniman</ets>; pref. <ets>be</ets> + <ets>niman</ets> to take. See
<er>Numb</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Benim</er>.]</ety> <def>To
make torpid; to deprive of sensation or sensibility; to stupefy; <as>as,
a hand or foot <ex>benumbed</ex> by cold</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The creeping death <qex>benumbed</qex> her senses first.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Benumbed</ent>⟦br⟧
